  "task": "# Relay stage 2: Research\nTask: use-composition-over-inheritance-for-custom-buttons\nWorking directory: /tmp/nix-shell.ZPB9Bm/visual-relay/wt/fbb5c78605a5/plan-20260630194022/use-composition-over-inheritance-for-custom-buttons\n\n## Task input\n# Use Composition Over Inheritance for Custom Buttons\n\nRecently, we had a task to create custom buttons and avoid the use of any plain button components. The intention was to avoid odd custom variations.\n\nHowever, there are still odd custom variations, such as the \"Save\" buttons next to the API keys in the settings screen.\n\nOne of the reasons for this is that the implementation inherits from buttons rather than creating new components that are composed of buttons.\n\nTo address this, we should make the button components be composed of buttons rather than inheriting from buttons.\n\nWe should also add a test that fails if a class is detected that inherits from button.\n\nThis would allow us to restrict the customizations allowed for a given button type so that only intentional variations are allowed and those variations are managed via fewer files.\n\n## Manifest\n(not set yet)\n\n## Task context\n### find-all-button-inheritance.png (23919 bytes, not inlined)\n\n### save-buttons-nonstandard-appearance.png (13483 bytes, not inlined)\n\n## Prior stages\n## Stage 1 - Ideate\n\n{\n  \"summary\": \"Refactor custom button components from class-based inheritance (extends Button) to composition-based wrappers, then enforce the pattern with an automated test (AST scan or ESLint rule) that fails on any file containing a class extending a button component. This eliminates the uncontrolled custom variations (e.g., nonstandard Save buttons) by limiting the props each button type exposes, centralizing style/behavior decisions in fewer files.\",\n  \"options\": [\n    \"Option A \u2014 'Props-Forwarding Wrapper': Convert each inherited button into a wrapper component that renders the base button internally, forwarding only a curated prop set. Add a Jest AST-sniffing test (regex /class \\\\w+ extends (Button|BaseButton)/) that fails on any inheritance match.\",\n    \"Option B \u2014 'Functional Component + Composition API' (Recommended): Rewrite all custom buttons as pure function components with a strict typed interface per button type. Add a custom ESLint rule (no-button-inheritance) that blocks any extends targeting a known button class, enforcing composition at the lint/type level.\",\n    \"Option C \u2014 'Decorator / HOC with Runtime Guard': Wrap existing class buttons in a HOC that restricts forwarded props; add a build-time or CI script that scans the AST for extends-button patterns and fails the build if any are found.\"\n  ]\n}\n\n\n\nEnd your reply with a single fenced ```json block, nothing after it, matching: { \"findings\": string, \"constraints\": string[] }",
